        <h1>General Rules For Admissions</h1>
        <font color="black">  <ol>
              <li> Applocations for admission must be present at the collage with the following documents:
                  <ul>
                      <li>  Residential proof.</li>
                      <li> Original university/board certificates and collage last attended by the applicant.</li>
                      <li>Character certificate from the head of the school or collage last attended by the applicant.</li>
                      <li>Eligibility certificate issued by GNDU to the student who have passed their qualifying examination from another institution except from PSEB, punjab university and punjabi university. for securing eligibility certificate, a candidate must aply on a prescribed from with a fee of Rs.300/- along with the following documents:
                          <ol>
                              <li>Original certificate and DMC of lower class passed.</li>
                              <li>Original migration certificate of the board/university from where a candidate has passed his/her lower examination.</li>
                          </ol>
                      </li>
                      <li>SC/ST candidates are to submit certificates from compitent authority.</li>
                      <li>For proficiency in sports/extra curricular activities, relevant certificates must be submitted.The last date for obtaining the eligibility certificate is as per GNDU guidelines.</li>
                  </ul>
              </li>
              <li> Candidates, whose application for admission are accepted provisionally, shall be considered only when they have  paid their dues and have made available to the collage office  the information that is lacking and fulfilled the condition stipulated for regular admission. While seeking  admission, a student must submit four latest pasport size photos along with his/her admission form, failing which his/her admission would considered invalid.</li>
               <li> The admission of candidate shall be deemed valid only if his/her deposite his/her fees and other dues in the college and obtains the roll number slip immediatly after the principal has puthis signature on the admission form granting his/her admission.</li>
               <li> Students , whose results are declared late  by the university/board or who seek admission  to technical  institutions but do not succeed therein, can join the college within ten days of publication of the results, as the case may be, without the payment of late fee fixed by the university/board as per rules. This however, is subject to availability of seats in college.</li>
               <li>Fees/dues once paid to the college shall not be refunded under any circumstances.</li>
               <li> The principal reserves with himself the right to grant or refuse admission to any student without assigning any reason thereto.</li>
               <li>Regular student of the college are not allowed to apear in the university examinations as private candidates.</li>
               <li> Student having passed the lower/qualifying examination through non-formal schmes shall not be allowed to join to the next higher class in the college as a regular student .</li>
               <li>No student shall be admitted to the first smester of B.A./B.Sc./B.Com./B.Com.(prof.)/B.Sc.(eco.)/BCA/B.Sc.(IT) unless he/she has successfully completed 12 years of schooling though an acceredited board/university.</li>
               <li>Only the following categories of students shall be allowed to take up basic punjabi in lieu general punjabi at the degree level:
                   <ul>
                       <li> Non resident indians or foreigh natinals.</li>
                       <li> Those who have passed Matric and Senior Examination with Pubjab History and culture in place of General punjabi.</li>
                       <li>Residents of other States of yhe Union of India whose mother tongue is not punjabi and who have not studied pubjabi at any level.</li>
                       <li>Those who are not domociles of the state of Punjab</li>
                   </ul>
               </li>
          </ol>
          <p>A student from any of the aforesaid categories shall jave to furnish to the College an affidevit, duly attested by the local Executive Magistrate, on a stamped paper deposing his/her entitlement to take up basic punjabi in lieu of general Punjabi at the time of Admission.

Note: The Principal reserves the right to lavy a uniform cess for meeting expenditure on unforeseen and emergent development project of College.</p>
       
